===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|手|alt1=扌|戈|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=hand}}.

Originally a variant form of {{zh-l|*划}}. Borrowed to mean a similar action.{{rfv-etym|zh}}

The popular interpretation as a hand ({{zh-l|*扌}}) looking for a halberd ({{zh-l|*戈}}) is a [[mnemonic]] and not the origin of the character.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=爪-“to seek”}}
Both “to seek” and “to give change” senses are attested since the Ming dynasty. The etymology is uncertain and it is unclear whether both senses are of the same origin. Compare {{zh-l|爪}} and {{zh-l|抓}}.

